    "text": "1946, Or-- no, 1945. [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] This is a picture taken in Bad Reichenhall of me, Jean Melzer, my husband, Morris Melzer, and my daughter, my first daughter, Sylvia, Sylvia Melzer, now Bergstein [LAUGHS] [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] This picture was taken in Kansas City, Missouri, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] me, my husband, and my daughter Sylvia and my daughter Rose. [PAUSES FOR 11 SECONDS] This is a picture taken in Breslau in 1946. On the first row on the back is my husband's sister [? Henia ?], his nephew, Aaron, Aaron [INAUDIBLE], and her husband, Isaac Shortz. In the second row from left to right is me, my husband, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Aaron, his sister's son, and the next is his sister's daughter. They all, the four of them survived. And this is two cousins, Joseph Schecter and Bella Schecter, brother and sister. [PAUSES FOR 22 SECONDS] This is also a picture taken in Breslau, and my husband's sister in the first row and her husband. The back row, the second row, is her son, Aaron. Next is me, my husband, and her daughter. Only the two are alive, me and the last one in the picture, lives in Israel now. [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] This is my daughter, Sylvia, and her husband Norman, my older daughter.",
